Being sensitive to the use of terms like 'spouse' and 'partner' in English,
I was quite surprise to run across the following today while translating a
newspaper article from 2001.

（彼女の）人生の伴侶も（歌手だと）。[kanozyo no zinsei no hanryo mo kasyu da to]

Wow. I had never encountered this phraseology in Japanese before. I love it.

