Chris,

奥さん cannot be used when referring to your own wife.  As a general
rule, you cannot add さん to yourself or your family, when addressing to
someone outside of your family.

奥さん is either the wife of whom you're speaking to, someone else's
wife, or the wife herself (the lady you're speaking to).

